						<p align="justify">
							The
							<b>
								Eclipse Persistence Services Project
								(EclipseLink)
							</b>
							project's goal is to provide an extensible
							framework that will enable Java developers
							to interact with relational databases, XML,
							and Enterprise Information Systems (EIS) in
							an efficient and productive manor.
							EclipseLink will focus on supporting leading
							persistence standards including the Java
							Persistence API (JPA), Java API for XML
							Binding (JAXB), Java Connector Architecture
							(JCA), and Service Data Objects (SDO).
						</p>

